operationalAddress.description: The primary physical address where the legal entity conducts its main business operations.

status.description: The current legal status of the entity (e.g., Active, Dissolved, In Liquidation).

fiscalYearEndMonth.description: The month in which the legal entity's fiscal year ends (1-12).

industryClassificationCode.description: A standard code (e.g., NAICS, SIC) classifying the entity's primary business sector.

primaryBusinessActivity.description: A brief description of the main type of business or operations conducted by the entity.

dateOfLastAnnualReturn.description: The date the legal entity last filed its required annual return or equivalent document with relevant authorities.

websiteURL.description: The official website address associated with the legal entity.

fulfillmentStatus.description: The current status of the order fulfillment process (e.g., Pending, Shipped, Delivered).

initiationDateTime.description: The date and time when the order fulfillment process was initiated.

completionDateTime.description: The date and time when the order fulfillment process was completed (e.g., shipped or delivered).

shippingCarrier.description: The name of the shipping carrier responsible for delivering the order.

trackingNumber.description: The tracking number provided by the shipping carrier for the shipment.

shippingMethod.description: The chosen method of shipping (e.g., Standard, Express, Next-Day).

estimatedDeliveryDate.description: The estimated date when the customer is expected to receive the order.

exchangeCompletionDateTime.description: The date and time the exchange event was finalized.

exchangeLocationDetails.description: Details about the physical or online location where the exchange was completed.

originalOrderId.description: Identifier of the original sales order associated with the item that was returned for exchange.

returnedItemReference.description: An identifier or reference for the item returned during the exchange (e.g., SKU, serial number).

exchangedItemReference.description: An identifier or reference for the item provided to the customer during the exchange (e.g., SKU, serial number).

priceDifferenceAmount.description: The monetary difference between the value of the exchanged item and the returned item, reflecting any amount paid or refunded.

priceDifferenceSettlementStatus.description: The status indicating how any price difference was settled (e.g., Paid, Refunded, Even).

currency.description: The currency in which the price is denominated (e.g., USD, EUR).

priceType.description: The type of price, such as 'Standard', 'Sale', 'MSRP', 'Wholesale', or 'Member Price'.

validFrom.description: The date and time from which this price is effective.

validUntil.description: The date and time until which this price is effective.

isTaxIncluded.description: Indicates whether the basePrice already includes applicable taxes.

taxRate.description: The percentage rate of tax applicable to the price, if not included.

unitOfMeasure.description: The unit of measure to which the price applies (e.g., 'EA' for each, 'LB' for pound, 'M' for meter).

name.description: The human-readable name of the subcategory.

description.description: A brief explanation or description of the subcategory's content.

slug.description: A URL-friendly identifier or path segment for the subcategory.

isActive.description: Indicates whether the subcategory is currently active or visible.

displayOrder.description: A numerical value used to determine the display order of subcategories within their parent category.

imageUrl.description: A URL or path to an image representing the subcategory.

createdAt.description: The date and time when the subcategory was created in the system.

receivedDateTime.description: The date and time when the goods were officially marked as received.

receivedByEmployeeID.description: Identifier of the employee who processed the goods reception.

receivingLocationID.description: Identifier of the specific physical location (e.g., dock, warehouse section) where the goods were received.

purchaseOrderNumber.description: The reference number of the purchase order associated with this goods received event.

packingSlipNumber.description: The number from the supplier's packing slip accompanying the received shipment.

carrierName.description: The name of the shipping carrier that delivered the goods.

conditionUponReceipt.description: A description or code indicating the physical condition of the received goods or packaging.

eventTimestamp.description: The date and time when the payment processing event occurred.

paymentMethodType.description: The type of payment instrument used for this payment (e.g., Credit Card, Cash, Gift Card, Mobile Wallet).

paymentAmount.description: The monetary value of the payment processed.

paymentCurrency.description: The currency code (e.g., USD, EUR) for the payment amount.

processingResult.description: The outcome status of the payment processing (e.g., Success, Failed, Declined, Pending).

processorTransactionId.description: The unique identifier assigned by the payment processor for this specific transaction.

salesTransactionId.description: A reference identifier linking this payment processing event to the associated sales transaction or order.

productReference.description: An identifier referencing the specific product or service covered by this contract line.

quantity.description: The number of units or quantity of the product or service agreed upon in this line item.

unitPrice.description: The agreed-upon price for a single unit of the product or service.

lineTotal.description: The total financial value for this specific contract line, typically calculated from quantity and unit price.

expectedDeliveryDate.description: The anticipated date for the delivery of the goods or completion of the service for this line.

lineDescription.description: A descriptive text providing further details about the product or service covered by this contract line.

lineStatus.description: The current status of this individual contract line within the overall contract.

approvalDateTime.description: The date and time when the return was officially approved.

approvedByUserID.description: The identifier of the user or system process that approved the return.

approvedRefundAmount.description: The total monetary amount approved to be refunded for the return.

refundMethod.description: The method by which the approved refund will be issued (e.g., original payment, store credit).

approvalNotes.description: Any additional notes or specific conditions related to the approval.

relatedReturnRequestID.description: The identifier of the original return request that this approval event relates to.

returnApprovalReason.description: A code or description indicating the specific reason or basis for the approval.

analysisDate.description: The date on which the planogram analysis was conducted.

storeID.description: The identifier for the store location where the analysis took place.

numberOfDiscrepancies.description: The total count of identified discrepancies or non-compliant items found during the analysis.

status.description: The current status of the planogram analysis report (e.g., 'Pending Review', 'Completed', 'Approved').

analystName.description: The name or identifier of the individual who performed the planogram analysis.

locationDescription.description: A description of the specific location within the store that was analyzed (e.g., 'Aisle 5', 'End Cap Display').

requiresAction.description: Indicates whether corrective action is required based on the analysis findings.

address.description: The primary physical address of the household.

householdSize.description: The total number of individuals residing in the household.

estimatedIncomeRange.description: An estimated category representing the household's annual income.

householdCreationDate.description: The date when the household was initially recorded in the system.

city.description: The city where the household is located.

postalCode.description: The postal or zip code associated with the household's address.

householdType.description: A classification indicating the typical structure or composition of the household (e.g., 'Family', 'Single Adult', 'Couple').

eventDateTime.description: The date and time when the item was added to the wishlist.

customerID.description: The unique identifier of the customer who performed the action.

productID.description: The unique identifier of the product added to the wishlist.

productVariantID.description: The unique identifier of the specific product variant (e.g., size, color) added, if applicable.

sourceChannel.description: The channel (e.g., 'Web', 'Mobile App') from which the action originated.

sessionID.description: The unique identifier for the user's browsing session during which the event occurred.

priceAtAddition.description: The price of the item at the time it was added to the wishlist.

methodName.description: The descriptive name of the refund method (e.g., 'Credit Card', 'Store Credit', 'Bank Transfer').

methodCategory.description: A categorization of the refund method (e.g., 'Electronic', 'Store Credit', 'Cash').

estimatedProcessingTimeDescription.description: A description of the typical time required to process a refund using this method (e.g., '3-5 business days').

hasAssociatedFees.description: Indicates whether processing a refund using this method incurs any fees for the customer or retailer.

applicabilityConditions.description: Describes any specific conditions or criteria under which this particular refund method can be applied.

isActive.description: Indicates if this refund method is currently available for use.

requiresCustomerInput.description: Indicates if the customer needs to provide additional details (like account number) for this refund method.

forecastedQuantity.description: The quantity of goods predicted by the forecast for a specific period or item.

forecastEffectiveDate.description: The date from which this forecast is considered valid or applies.

procurementOrderQuantity.description: The actual quantity of goods ordered from the supplier.

supplierLeadTimeDays.description: The estimated number of days required for delivery after placing a procurement order.

expectedArrivalDate.description: The anticipated date when the procured goods are expected to arrive at the designated location.

procurementStatus.description: The current state of the procurement and logistics process (e.g., 'Pending Order', 'Ordered', 'In Transit', 'Received').

estimatedLogisticsCost.description: The estimated cost associated with transportation and logistics for this procurement batch.

startDate.description: The official start date of the planning season.

endDate.description: The official end date of the planning season.

fiscalYear.description: The fiscal year to which the planning season belongs.

seasonCode.description: An internal code or identifier used to reference the planning season.

calendarSeason.description: The standard calendar season (e.g., Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter, Holiday) that this planning season aligns with.

overallBudget.description: The total planned budget allocated for this planning season.

description.description: A detailed description providing context or notes about the planning season.

itemSKUID.description: The unique identifier for the specific product or SKU to which this safety stock applies.

locationID.description: The unique identifier for the store, warehouse, or location to which this safety stock applies.

targetServiceLevel.description: The desired probability of satisfying customer demand from on-hand inventory, used in safety stock calculation.

calculationMethod.description: Describes the method or formula used to calculate this safety stock quantity.

calculationDateTime.description: The date and time when this specific safety stock quantity was calculated or last updated.

validFromDate.description: The date from which this safety stock quantity is considered active or valid.

validToDate.description: The date until which this safety stock quantity is considered active or valid.

hexCode.description: The hexadecimal representation of the color, often used in digital and web contexts.

rgbValue.description: The RGB (Red, Green, Blue) representation of the color, typically stored as a formatted string.

pantoneCode.description: The standard Pantone color code corresponding to this color.

swatchImageUrl.description: A URL pointing to an image file displaying a visual swatch of the color.

shadeCategory.description: A broad classification of the color based on its lightness or darkness, such as 'Light', 'Medium', or 'Dark'.

finish.description: Describes the surface finish associated with the color, such as 'Matte', 'Glossy', or 'Metallic'.

isPrimaryColor.description: Indicates if this color is considered the main or primary color in contexts where multiple colors might be listed.

effectiveStartDate.description: The date from which this non-peak period definition is active.

effectiveEndDate.description: The date until which this non-peak period definition is active.

startTimeOfDay.description: The specific time of day when the non-peak period begins (e.g., '09:00').

endTimeOfDay.description: The specific time of day when the non-peak period ends (e.g., '17:00').

applicableDaysOfWeek.description: Specifies which days of the week this non-peak period applies to (e.g., 'Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday').

isRecurring.description: Indicates if the non-peak period definition is scheduled to repeat based on a pattern.

notes.description: Additional notes or context about this non-peak period definition.

overrideDateTime.description: The date and time when the price override occurred.

productIdentifier.description: An identifier for the product whose price was overridden (e.g., SKU, UPC).

originalPrice.description: The price of the product before the override was applied.

newPrice.description: The final price of the product after the override was applied.

overrideReason.description: A description or code explaining why the price override was performed.

employeeIdentifier.description: An identifier for the employee who performed the price override.

transactionIdentifier.description: An identifier for the transaction during which the price override occurred.

originalSaleID.description: The unique identifier of the original sale transaction that was voided.

voidTimestamp.description: The date and time when the sale voiding event occurred.

voidReason.description: A description or code indicating the reason why the sale was voided.

voidingUserID.description: The identifier of the user, employee, or system that initiated the voiding process.

voidedAmount.description: The total monetary value of the sale that was voided.

storeID.description: The identifier of the retail store where the sale voiding event took place.

terminalID.description: The identifier of the point-of-sale terminal used for the voiding transaction.

sellDateTime.description: The exact date and time the sale transaction was completed.

locationID.description: Identifier for the physical store or location where the sale took place.

customerID.description: Identifier for the customer who completed the purchase, if available (e.g., loyalty program member).

totalAmount.description: The total monetary value of the sale transaction, including taxes and after discounts.

taxAmount.description: The total amount of tax charged for the entire transaction.

discountAmount.description: The total monetary value of discounts applied to the entire transaction.

paymentMethod.description: The method used by the customer to pay for the transaction (e.g., "Credit Card", "Cash", "Debit", "Gift Card").

deviceType.description: Categorizes the device type, such as 'mobile', 'tablet', 'desktop', or 'smartwatch'.

operatingSystem.description: Specifies the operating system running on the device, like 'iOS', 'Android', 'Windows', or 'macOS'.

browser.description: Identifies the web browser used on the device for accessing retail services.

lastActivityDateTime.description: Records the date and time when this device was last used or seen interacting with the retail system.

firstSeenDateTime.description: Records the date and time when this device was first associated with the customer profile.

pushNotificationToken.description: A unique token used by push notification services to send messages to this specific device.

modelName.description: Provides the specific model name of the device, such as 'iPhone 14 Pro' or 'Galaxy S23'.

productID.description: Identifier for the product or SKU associated with this reorder point.

locationID.description: Identifier for the specific retail location or warehouse where this reorder point is applied.

averageDailyDemand.description: The calculated average daily demand used in determining the reorder point quantity.

leadTimeDays.description: The expected number of days for stock replenishment lead time used in determining the reorder point.

safetyStockQty.description: The quantity of safety stock included in the reorder point calculation.

calculationMethod.description: Describes the method or formula used to calculate the reorder point quantity.

effectiveStartDate.description: The date from which this specific reorder point quantity becomes effective.

deliveryMethodName.description: The human-readable name of the delivery method (e.g., Standard Shipping, Express, Click & Collect).

estimatedDeliveryTime.description: The estimated time frame for delivery (e.g., '2-3 business days', 'Next Day').

baseCost.description: The base price associated with using this delivery method.

serviceProvider.description: The name of the external service provider or carrier responsible for this delivery method (e.g., USPS, FedEx, Internal).

methodType.description: A classification indicating the broad category of the delivery method (e.g., 'Shipping', 'Pickup', 'Digital').

cutoffTime.description: The time of day by which an order must be placed for this method to be processed for timely delivery (e.g., '3 PM EST').

addressStreet.description: The street address of the store location.

addressCity.description: The city where the store is located.

addressStateProvince.description: The state or province where the store is located.

addressPostalCode.description: The postal or zip code for the store location.

country.description: The country where the store is located.

phoneNumber.description: The main contact phone number for the store.

openingDate.description: The date the store location officially opened for business.

description.description: Provides a detailed explanation of what the status represents.

sequenceOrder.description: Indicates the typical sequential position of this status in the purchase order lifecycle.

isTerminalStatus.description: Specifies whether this status represents a final or completed state for a purchase order.

isActive.description: Indicates whether this status code is currently considered active and available for use.

createdDate.description: The date on which this purchase order status definition was created.

lastUpdatedDate.description: The date on which this purchase order status definition was last modified.

searchQuery.description: The text string entered by the customer in the search bar.

searchTimestamp.description: The date and time when the customer performed the search.

numberOfResults.description: The count of search results returned for the query.

searchSuccessful.description: Indicates whether the search yielded any results (True) or none (False).

searchInitiationContext.description: The page or context from which the search was initiated (e.g., 'Homepage', 'CategoryPage').

customerSessionId.description: An identifier for the customer's browsing session during which the search occurred.

deviceType.description: The type of device the customer used to perform the search (e.g., 'Desktop', 'Mobile', 'Tablet').

regionName.description: The human-readable name of the retail region.

country.description: The country in which the region is located.

stateProvince.description: The state or province within the country for this region.

population.description: The estimated population within the geographical boundaries of the region, relevant for market analysis.

latitude.description: The latitude coordinate for the approximate geographic center of the region.

longitude.description: The longitude coordinate for the approximate geographic center of the region.

establishmentDate.description: The date when this retail region was officially defined or created within the system.

price.description: The selling price for this specific product variant.

stockQuantity.description: The current number of units available in stock for this variant.

gtin.description: The Global Trade Item Number (e.g., EAN, UPC) uniquely identifying this product variant.

color.description: The specific color attribute of this product variant.

size.description: The specific size attribute of this product variant.

weight.description: The weight of a single unit of this variant, typically used for shipping calculations.

mainImageUrl.description: A URL pointing to the primary image representing this specific product variant.

streetAddress.description: The primary street address line of the location.

city.description: The city where the location is situated.

stateProvince.description: The state or province where the location is situated.

postalCode.description: The postal or zip code for the location.

country.description: The country where the location is situated.

latitude.description: The geographical latitude coordinate of the location.

longitude.description: The geographical longitude coordinate of the location.
